{
  "stem": "26276.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You took off the jacket, you didn't have to wear the band, because you were in the house.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I was already in my own home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mhm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, every day something different.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would close down most of the stores.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The bakeries-- they left them open certain hours so they should be able to bake bread for the next day.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then people would come by.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was a military-- you know, German soldiers right in the doorway there to watch, that told the baker how much to give to the person-- you know, half pound bread or a pound bread.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember they sliced up breads in little pieces.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You had to pay for it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But that's all you were allowed to get.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that baker in our street-- like, when I was outside, and I saw that there are no German staying near it, I would go in and ask him if he has any  more bread left that I could take.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Once in a  while, he gave me even a whole bread.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I would put it under my jacket and try to walk home with it so we should have more to eat the next day.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, from the beginning, there was not much, except they took people out of the house to do some cleaning in the streets, cleaning in the places where there stayed the Germans.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After the end of the day, they would allow you to go back home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But later on, a few months later, one of the German police in the street would come over to me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He would grab my arm and take me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I thought that he is going to arrest me.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
